This paper discusses the architecture of IoT networks and the technologies used to support them. The most relevant sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the design and implementation of communication networks. The paper also discusses the use of data analytics and big data, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of advanced spectrum sharing and interference management is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with the efficient use of resources in distributed systems. The paper also discusses the use of machine-type communication and wireless network function virtualization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile edge computing and mobile cloud computing, which falls under cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) as it deals with the use of mobile devices in virtual environments.
